==English==

===Etymology===
Via {{OF.}} {{term|epiphanie}}, {{L.}} {{term|epiphania}} from {{etyl|grc}} {{term|sc=polytonic|ἐπιφάνεια|tr=epiphaneia||manifestation, striking appearance}}, {{term|sc=polytonic|-εια|tr=-eia}} feminine of {{term|sc=polytonic|ἐπιφαίνω|tr=epiphaionō||I appear, display}} ({{term|sc=polytonic|ἐπι||upon|tr=epi}} + {{term|sc=polytonic|φαίνω|tr=phainō||I shine, appear}}. English [[Epiphany]] (of Christ) since the 14th century, generic use since the 17th century.

